---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { servicePricingFaqs } from '../../data/pricing';
import PageIntro from '../../components/PageIntro.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Restaurant Review Management Toronto | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Restaurant review management in Toronto. Get more 5-star reviews, respond to every review professionally, and turn your reputation into your best marketing channel. The GTA's only restaurant review specialist."
>

  <main>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <PageIntro title="Restaurant Review Management Toronto" description="Your reviews are your reputation. We build systems that generate more 5-star reviews, respond to every review professionally, and turn your online reputation into your most powerful marketing channel."  ctaLabel="Book a Free Google Audit" ctaHref="/contact/" />

    <!-- THE NUMBERS -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          Why Reviews Matter More Than Anything Else
        </h2>
        <p>
          Before someone visits your restaurant, they check your reviews. Every single time. Here's what the data shows.
        </p>

        <div class="trg-stat-grid">
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">93%</div>
            <div class="label">of diners read online reviews before choosing a restaurant</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">4.2</div>
            <div class="label">minimum star rating before most people will consider visiting</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">53%</div>
            <div class="label">of customers won't visit a business with less than 4 stars</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          Reviews aren't just social proof. They're a direct ranking factor for Google Maps. Restaurants with more reviews, higher ratings, and recent review activity rank higher in local search. Your reviews are simultaneously your best marketing and your best SEO.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          Your Reviews Are Working Against You
        </h2>
        <p>
          You've poured everything into your restaurant — the menu, the ambiance, the service. But online, your reputation tells a different story. Here's what we see with most restaurants that come to us.
        </p>

        <h3>Bad reviews are sitting unanswered</h3>
        <p>
          You got a 1-star review three months ago from someone who waited too long for their food. It's still sitting there with no response. Every potential customer who reads it sees a restaurant that doesn't care. Studies show that 45% of consumers are more likely to visit a business that responds to negative reviews. Your silence is louder than the complaint.
        </p>

        <h3>You have no system to generate good reviews</h3>
        <p>
          Your happiest customers leave your restaurant thinking "that was amazing" and then... nothing. They don't leave a review because nobody asked them to. The only people motivated enough to leave reviews on their own are the ones who had a bad experience. Without a proactive review generation system, your online reputation will always lag behind the actual quality of your restaurant.
        </p>

        <h3>Your review count is stagnant</h3>
        <p>
          You have 47 Google reviews. Your competitor across the street has 340. Even if your average rating is higher, Google sees their review velocity and volume as a stronger trust signal. They rank higher. They get more visibility. They get more customers. And those customers leave more reviews, creating a flywheel effect that pushes you further behind every month.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>What You Get</h2>
        <p>
          We build a complete review management ecosystem for your restaurant. Not just monitoring — active systems that generate reviews, respond professionally, and protect your reputation.
        </p>

        <h3>Review Response System</h3>
        <p>
          Every review on Google, Yelp, and TripAdvisor gets a professional, personalized response within 24 hours. Not generic copy-paste templates — actual thoughtful responses that address the specific feedback.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Positive review responses</strong> — We thank reviewers by name, reference specific details from their visit, and invite them back.</li>
          <li><strong>Negative review responses</strong> — We acknowledge the concern, apologize appropriately, offer to make it right, and move the conversation offline.</li>
          <li><strong>Fake review flagging</strong> — We monitor for fake reviews, competitor sabotage, and policy-violating content and file removal requests.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="trg-callout">
          <p><strong>Example negative review response:</strong> "Hi Sarah, thank you for sharing your experience. I'm sorry the wait time didn't meet the standard we hold ourselves to — that's not the experience we want anyone to have at [Restaurant]. I'd love the chance to make it right. Could you reach out to me directly at [email]? We'd like to invite you back on us. — [Owner Name]"</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Review Generation System</h3>
        <p>
          The most important part of review management isn't responding to reviews — it's generating new ones. We implement multiple touchpoints that make it effortless for happy customers to leave a review.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Table-side QR codes</strong> — Custom-branded QR code cards placed on every table that link directly to your Google review page. One scan, one tap, done.</li>
          <li><strong>Automated follow-up texts</strong> — Automated text messages sent 2 hours after the dining experience. Our follow-up messages achieve a 15-22% review conversion rate.</li>
          <li><strong>Staff training program</strong> — We train your servers and hosts on when, how, and whom to ask for reviews.</li>
          <li><strong>Receipt and bill insert prompts</strong> — A subtle review prompt printed on receipts or included as a card with the bill.</li>
          <li><strong>Post-event and catering follow-up</strong> — For restaurants that host events or do catering, we create follow-up sequences specifically for these high-satisfaction moments.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Reputation Monitoring</h3>
        <p>
          We don't just monitor Google. We monitor every platform where your restaurant might be reviewed — Google, Yelp, TripAdvisor, Instagram, Facebook, and halal-specific platforms like Zabihah.com for halal restaurants.
        </p>

        <h3>Crisis Response Protocol</h3>
        <p>
          Every restaurant will eventually face a review crisis. We have a protocol ready before it happens — rapid response within 2 hours for crisis-level reviews, social media monitoring, and a documented escalation playbook.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span>1</span><strong>Audit</strong></p>
          <p>We analyze your current review landscape across every platform: total review count, average rating, review velocity, response rate, sentiment patterns, and competitor benchmarks.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span>2</span><strong>Plan</strong></p>
          <p>We design a custom review management strategy based on your restaurant's specific situation. You approve everything before we implement a single thing.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
          <p><span>3</span><strong>Execute</strong></p>
          <p>We install the review generation systems, begin monitoring and responding to every review within 24 hours, train your staff, and deploy QR codes and follow-up sequences. Most restaurants see a 300–500% increase in monthly review volume within the first 60 days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CASE STUDY -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Real Results</h2>

        <div class="trg-card-dark-accent">
          <p>47 reviews to 280+ in 6 months</p>
          <p>Crab Boil had 47 Google reviews with a 4.1-star average when they came to us. We implemented table-side QR codes, automated follow-up texts, and staff training. Within 6 months, their review count grew to over 280, their average rating climbed to 4.5 stars, and their Google Maps ranking jumped from position 8 to position 2 for "seafood restaurant Toronto."</p>
          <p><a href="/case-studies/crab-boil/">Read the full Crab Boil case study</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How much does restaurant review management cost in Toronto?</h3>
          <p>{servicePricingFaqs.reviews}</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Can you remove bad reviews from Google?</h3>
          <p>No one can remove legitimate reviews from Google — anyone who tells you otherwise is lying. What we can do is flag reviews that violate Google's policies for removal. More importantly, our strategy focuses on generating enough genuine positive reviews that negative ones become statistically insignificant.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How do you get more reviews for my restaurant?</h3>
          <p>We implement a multi-touch review generation system: table-side QR codes, automated follow-up texts sent 2 hours after dining, trained staff who know when and how to ask, and receipt prompts. Most restaurants see a 300–500% increase in monthly review volume within the first 60 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How long does it take to see results?</h3>
          <p>You'll see immediate results in two areas: response time (every review gets a professional response within 24 hours from day one) and review volume (our generation systems typically double or triple monthly reviews within 30 days). The compounding effects on Google ranking build over 3–6 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Your Reputation Is Already Being Written</h2>
        <p>
          The question isn't whether people are talking about your restaurant online. They are. The question is whether you're shaping the conversation or letting it shape itself.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/">
          Book a Free Google Audit
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
